This software is provided as a reference implementation and educational
resource for Zero Trust Architecture in IoMT environments. It is NOT a
certified medical device or medical software product. It has not been
evaluated, reviewed, or approved by the U.S. Food and Drug Administration
(FDA), the European Medicines Agency (EMA), or any other regulatory body.

Organizations implementing this architecture in production healthcare
environments are responsible for:

1. Conducting their own security assessment and risk analysis
2. Ensuring compliance with applicable regulations (HIPAA, GDPR, etc.)
3. Validating that the implementation meets their clinical and operational
   requirements
4. Obtaining any required regulatory approvals for their specific deployment

The authors make no warranties regarding the fitness of this software for
use in clinical environments and accept no liability for patient harm,
data breaches, or regulatory violations arising from its use.

For production healthcare deployments, engage qualified healthcare
cybersecurity professionals and ensure compliance with your organization's
security policies and applicable regulatory requirements.
